Column Comment.0: CLASSIFICATION: SYSTEM: Identifies and describes the classification system thatis used. The UNSPSC code set is a useful and practical source of classificationinformation.
Column Comment.1: CLASSIFICATION LEVEL IDENTIFIER: Unique identifier used to capture the level inclassification systems, such as those that describe types of equipment. A number ofclassification schemes are availabe, including the UNSPSC code set. Typically, theseclassification systems are hierarchical. Objects may be classified at any level of theclassification system, and through more than one classification system.
Column Comment.2: CLASSIFICATION LEVEL ALIAS IDENTIFIER: Unique identifier for an alternatename, code or identifier for a classification system level. We recommend that allnames, codes and identifiers be stored in this table and denormalized elsewhere asrequired by performance or other issues.
Column Comment.3: ABBREVIATION: Abbreviation used for reference type or code.
Column Comment.4: ACTIVE INDICATOR: A Y/N flag indicating whether this row of data is currently eitheractive / valid (Y) or inactive / invalid (N).
Column Comment.5: CLASSIFICATION SYSTEM ALIAS NAME: The name assigned to the classificaitonsystem in this alias version.
Column Comment.6: ALIAS REASON: The reason why the alias was created, such as governmentchange, assigned by application etc.
Column Comment.7: ALIAS SHORT NAME: Short name given to this alias.
Column Comment.8: ALIAS TYPE: The type of alias, such as partner, historical, records etc
Column Comment.9: ALIAS VERSION: The version number assigned in this alias system.
Column Comment.10: AMENDED DATE: the date on which a name has been ammended. Often, this isused for official or legal changes to a name.
Column Comment.11: COLUMN NAME: the name of a column in a database schema.
Column Comment.12: CREATED DATE: The date on which the alias was first created. This date maypreceed the ammendment date, in the event that the ammended date refers to aformal registration event.
Column Comment.13: EFFECTIVE DATE: date on which the data in this row came into effect.
Column Comment.14: EXPIRY DATE: Date on which the data in this row of data was no longer in effect.
Column Comment.15: LANGUAGE IDENTIFIER: The language of the alias.
Column Comment.16: ORIGINAL INDICATOR: A y/n flag indicating that this alias is the original one firstassigned to a business object.
Column Comment.17: CLASSIFICATION SYSTEM ALIAS OWNER: the business associate who is theowner or custodian of the alias for the classification system level.
Column Comment.18: ROW_MANAGEMENT_GUID: This value may be used to provide a global uniqueidentifier for this row of data. Use of this column is not mandatory, but if used,optional PPDM NOT NULL and UNIQUE INDEX constraints provided in the datamodel DDL should be created.
Column Comment.19: PREFERRED INDICATOR: A Y/N flag indicating that this alias version is thepreferred for usual use. If you wish, the preferred version may be replicated in theCLASS SYSTEM table for ease of query and reporting.
Column Comment.20: REASON DESCRIPTION: A narrative explanation about the alias being used.
Column Comment.21: REFERENCED GUID: the GUID in the reference like table that is included in theclassification. Use this to identify how the values in a reference table fit into ahierarchy of values.
Column Comment.22: REMARK: Narrative remarks about this row of data.
Column Comment.23: SCHEMA ENTITY IDENTIFIER: Unique identifier for an entity or object in an XML orEDI schema.
Column Comment.24: SOURCE: The individual, company, state, or government agency designated as thesource of information for this row.
Column Comment.25: SOURCE DOCUMENT: Foreign key from the table that captures bibliographic orsource information. This could be a URL, book, publication or other document.
Column Comment.26: STRUCK OFF DATE: Date on which the legal name was struck from corporateregistry and is no longer used.
Column Comment.27: APPLICATION NAME: The name of the software application that uses this alias.
Column Comment.28: SYSTEM IDENTIFIER: A unique identifier for a data storage system, such as adatabase or XML schema.
Column Comment.29: SYSTEM TABLE NAME: the name of a table in a database schema.
Column Comment.30: USE RULE: A narrative column that is used to describe the circumstances in whichthis alias is to be used.
Column Comment.31: ROW CHANGED BY: Application login id of the user who last changed the row.
Column Comment.32: ROW CHANGED DATE: System date of the last time the row was changed.
Column Comment.33: ROW CREATED BY: System user who created this row of data.
Column Comment.34: ROW CREATED DATE: Date that the row was created on.
Column Comment.35: ROW_EFFECTIVE_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of datais effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row of data wasmade available to end users, for example.
Column Comment.36: ROW_EXPIRY_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of data isno longer effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row ofdata was no longer available to end users, for example.
Column Comment.37: PPDM ROW QUALITY: A set of values indicating the quality of data in this row,usually with reference to the method or procedures used to load the data, althoughother types of quality reference are permitted.
